Package com.stormpath.sdk.idsite

Interface Summary
AccountResult Represents the result of an ID Site callback redirect, obtained after the end-user has used the ID Site and has been returned to an application's callbackUri.
AuthenticationResult Holder for Authentication-specific data that will be received on the IdSiteResultListener#onAuthenticated(AuthenticationResult) method.
IdSiteCallbackHandler Handles HTTP replies sent from your ID Site to your application's callbackUri, for example, https://awesomeapp.com/id, and returns an AccountResult.
IdSiteResultListener Listener interface to get notifications about effective operations of the Id Site invocation: registration, authentication or logout.
IdSiteUrlBuilder Helps build a URL you can use to redirect your application users to a hosted login/registration/forgot-password site - what Stormpath calls an 'Identity Site' (or 'ID Site' for short) - for performing common user identity functionality.
LogoutResult Holder for Logout-specific data that will be received on the IdSiteResultListener#onLogout(LogoutResult) method.
Nonce A cryptographic nonce representation for values that cannot be used more than once.
NonceStore Store nonce values and provides methods to check if a nonce has already been used, and to add it to the nonceStore to ensure that the same nonce cannot be used again.
RegistrationResult Holder for Registration-specific data that will be received on the IdSiteResultListener#onRegistered(RegistrationResult) method.
